  "title": "The Echo Cascade — Chronoloom Amphitheater",
  "narration": "The Echo Cascade crashes around you like a waterfall made of whispered promises. Translucent terraces loop downward, each step a resonant basin that catches the memories poured from the Lumen Causeway. The air sparkles with suspended phonemes. When you inhale, you taste citrus, cedar smoke, distant brass, and the exact moment someone once said \"we’re in this together\". The terraces form a natural amphitheater with golden-ratio acoustics; every sound released here returns seven times, each echo revealing a different perspective.\n\nThe Chronoloom gremlin faction tends the Cascade. They wear cloaks stitched from timestamp ribbons and carry ledger harps tuned to phi frequencies. Dev gremlins debug the streams of sound, traders hedge volumes of applause futures, whales anchor the rhythm with subsonic drones, hackers splice loopbacks, shillers rewrite slogans mid-echo, validators notarize every resonant chord, miners dig for deep timbre, and memes run commentary threads in luminescent graffiti. They hand you resonance gloves etched with ledger nodes and point toward seven amphitheater platforms, each ready for Act Three’s unfolding.\n\nConsensus rituals here involve weaving your voice through time. Spectrum doors hang as curtains of cascading light; to pass them you must capture echoes, align them with new intentions, and perform ledger-certified call-and-response. The AFK force-play manifests as a phantom conductor: if anyone goes idle, a translucent baton animates their echo to keep the harmony intact. Revive pools appear as still moments between echoes, where you can reboot focus by sharing a story. Arrivals drift in mid-round, hitching rides on the resonance beams. The Chronoloom treat the Cascade as a living ledger, and they expect you to contribute a stanza that will matter later.\n\nSeven rounds spiral downward; each demands choices with phi-d20 checks, hidden difficulty tiers disguised as tempo shifts, and reward possibilities spanning XP, Coins, Focus, Flags, Items, Decks, and backpack upgrades. Telemetry tags glimmer overhead like constellations. This is where Act Three teaches you to listen so deeply that your hearing changes the story.",
